The paper deals with capacity limits of real-time streaming over a broadcast channel, which involves information theory and networking concepts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the transmission of packets over a network, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The study of capacity as a function of burst-lengths and delays at the two receivers involves the analysis of data structures and algorithms, which is covered under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the study of the operation of the system in different regimes, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves the construction of codes and converse techniques, which is covered under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
